Startup Lawyer recommendation (Not top 10)
text:
For my last company, I used Orrick.

Starting a new company now and I see no need to pay 15K for incorporation - even if it's deferred. I may never raise money and even if I did, I wont want to pay someone 15K for a job that's probably 1K.

I'm looking for a lawyer who's decent, will use standard docs (perhaps the ones from my last company that Orrick registered), do some other paperwork and do it for a reasonable price.

Any advice or law firm recommendations to get this done quickly and cheaply?

I'm also ok giving my older docs to an accountant and have them do the work for me. Is that ok or stupid?

Anything YC does here to help (and no YC companies can use it)?

Show HN: Cross-platform network analyser developed in Rust
text:
In the past months I developed an open source, cross-platform application to help people monitor their personal Internet traffic.

The application is thought to be easy-to-use and therefore can be used even if you don't have a strong networking experience.

I'm currently maintaining the project, implementing new features such as geolocation of the addresses, customisable notifications to alert the user when specific events occur and a deeper inspection page to retrieve more details about each connection.

The whole application, including the GUI, is developed using the Rust language.

If you have any consideration, I'd be glad to hear feedbacks about the app or suggestions for new features.

Feel free to open an issue on GitHub or drop a comment here!
